Titolo: Action Quest

Anno: 1982

Descrizione: Action Quest is a video game written by Jack Verson for the Atari 8-bit family. It was published in 1982 by his company, JV Software. Action Quest combines real-time action with puzzle solving as the player explores 30 rooms in an attempt to collect 20 treasures. Reviewers found the combination to be different from how puzzles in games—such as graphic adventures—worked at the time.

Genere: Action-adventure 

Valutazione: N/A
